    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It is an common anti-pattern for developers starting to use assertions for the first time to put all their defense into assertions, leaving code which will literally crash at runtime in the absence of the assertions.   Missing null-pointer checks are a key example.\n\n`Writing Solid Code` - now over 20 years old was where I first saw these kind of defensive programming practices explored at depth for the first time.\n\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Writing-Solid-Code-20th-Anniversary/dp/1570740550\n",
