    "body": "When I verify the lack of assertion failures in theorem provers, I would want to see `assert(thing)` compiled into `if (!thing) invalid_opcode` rather than `if (!thing) throw;`.  I don't want to prove \"no `throw` is ever executed\" (because users can specify wrong function signatures) but \"no invalid opcodes are ever executed\" is provable (if assertions never fail).\r\n\r\nI'm suspicious of optionally compiled anything.",
